{{Main|2008 World Wheelchair Curling Championship}}
The '''qualification event''' for the '''[[2007 World Wheelchair Curling Championship]]''' was held from November 8 to 12, 2006 at the [[Braehead Curling Rink]] in [[Braehead]], [[Scotland]]. The event's two top finishers, Russia and Japan, both qualified to participate in the 2008 World Wheelchair Curling Championship. The two qualification spots were given to the top two teams at the conclusion of the [[Round-robin tournament|round robin]].

