'''2018 in film''' is an overview of events, including the highest-grossing films, award ceremonies, festivals, and a list of films released and notable deaths.
==Highest-grossing films== {{see also|Lists of box office number-one films#2018}}
The top films released in 2018 by worldwide gross are as follows:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2018&p=.htm| title=2018 Yearly Box Office Results|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=July 1, 2018}}</ref> <!-- Note: We only link the distributor ONCE --> {| class="wikitable" style="margin:auto; margin:auto;" |+Highest-grossing films of 2018 |- ! Rank!! Title !! Distributor !! Worldwide gross <!--ONLY FILMS RELEASED FIRST IN 2018 WILL BE ADDED ON THIS LIST--> |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 1 | ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' | rowspan="2" | [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Disney]] | $2,046,909,636 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 2 | ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]'' | $1,346,913,161 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 3 | ''[[Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom]]'' | [[Universal Pictures|Universal]] | $1,304,944,060 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 4 | ''[[Incredibles 2]]'' | Disney | $1,240,875,074 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 5 | ''[[Venom (2018 film)|Venom]]'' | [[Sony Pictures]] | $843,970,652 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 6 |''[[Mission: Impossible – Fallout]]'' | [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]] | $791,017,452 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 7 | ''[[Deadpool 2]]'' | [[20th Century Fox]] | $734,245,921 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 8 | ''[[Ant-Man and the Wasp]]'' | Disney | $622,606,228 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 9 | ''[[Ready Player One (film)|Ready Player One]]'' | [[Warner Bros.]] | $582,218,455 |- ! style="text-align:center;"| 10 | ''[[2.0. (film)|2.0.]]'' | [[Dharma Productions]] | $579,220,560 |}
''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' grossed $2 billion worldwide, becoming the fourth movie to surpass the milestone, and [[List of highest-grossing films|4th highest-grossing film of all time]]. ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]'', ''[[Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom]]'' and ''[[Incredibles 2]]'' have each grossed over $1 billion worldwide, and are the 9th, 12th and 15th highest-grossing films, with the latter becoming the [[List of highest-grossing animated films|2nd highest-grossing animated film of all time]].
===2018 box office records=== * The [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] became the [[List of highest-grossing franchises and film series|first film franchise]] to gross more than $14{{nbsp}}billion with the release of ''Black Panther'',<ref>{{cite web|first=Sean|last=Gerber|url=https://marvelstudiosnews.com/2018/02/22/marvel-studios-now-earned-14-billion-worldwide-less-10-years|title=Marvel Studios has now earned over $14 billion worldwide in less than 10 years|publisher=marvelstudiosnews.com|date=February 22, 2018|accessdate=February 24, 2018}}</ref> and the first franchise to release five billion-dollar-grossing films (with ''Black Panther'' joining ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'', ''[[Iron Man 3]]'', ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'', and ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]''). Two months later, the MCU became the first film franchise to gross more than $15{{nbsp}}billion and $16{{nbsp}}billion with the release of ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'', which became the sixth billion-dollar-grossing film in the franchise,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2411802/the-mcu-just-hit-a-huge-box-office-milestone|title=The MCU Just Hit A Huge Box Office Milestone|last=Wood|first=Matt|date=April 29, 2018|publisher=Cinema Blend}}</ref> and also the first film in the franchise to earn $2 billion. Two months after that, the MCU became the first film franchise to gross over $17{{nbsp}}billion with the release of ''[[Ant-Man and the Wasp]]''. * [[China]] set an all-time biggest global one-month record in February with RMB 10.14 billion ($1.6 billion), calculating revenues from both local and foreign films. The record breaking number was largely attributed to the [[Lunar New Year]] holiday. The previous global monthly box office record was set in July 2011 in North America with $1.395 billion and the previous highest-grossing month in China was August 2017 with RMB 7.38 billion ($1.17 billion).<ref>{{cite web|url= http://deadline.com/2018/03/china-box-office-global-monthly-record-february-2018-1202312183/amp/|title= China Sets One-Month Box Office Record With $1.6B February|author=Nancy Tartaglione|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 6, 2018|accessdate=March 7, 2018}}</ref> The highest-grossing films in China during the month were the local [[Chinese films]] ''[[Operation Red Sea]]'', ''[[Monster Hunt 2]]'', and ''[[Detective Chinatown 2]]'', and the foreign [[Indian film]] ''[[Secret Superstar]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=How Aamir Khan's Secret Superstar contributed to China's global, record-breaking box-office collections|url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/how-aamir-khans-secret-superstar-contributed-to-chinas-global-record-breaking-box-office-collections-4379827.html|accessdate=March 7, 2018|work=[[Firstpost]]}}</ref> * For the first time in history, February recorded $1 billion ticket sales in North America, fueled largely by the success of Disney/Marvel's ''Black Panther'' which represented 43% or $428.8 million of the entire month's ticket sales. The previous February record was in 2012 with $818.4 million.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://deadline.com/2018/03/black-panther-february-box-office-1202311491/|title= February Box Office Hits All-Time Record Of $1 Billion Fueled By 'Black Panther'|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 5, 2018|accessdate=March 7, 2018}}</ref> * In China, the combined opening weekend numbers of ''Monster Hunt 2'' (US$190 million), ''Detective Chinatown 2'' (US$154 million), ''[[The Monkey King 3]]'' (US$79.9 million), ''Operation Red Sea'' (US$70.3 million) and ''Boonie Bears: The Big Shrink'' (US$40.9 million) amounted to a record breaking RMB3.21 billion (US$506 million) or US$543 million weekend with online ticket sales, which is more than double the feat achieved in 2017 (US$205 million) and 2016 (US$224 million) during the same time period.<ref name="190M">{{cite web|url= https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/monster-hunt-2-190-million-china-enjoys-half-billion-dollar-weekend-1202703946/amp/|title= 'Monster Hunt 2' Scores $190 Million as China Enjoys Half Billion Dollar Weekend|author=Patrick Frater|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=February 18, 2018|accessdate=February 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://twitter.com/chinaboxoffice/status/965268486057594881|title=China Box Office tweet|accessdate=February 19, 2018|date=2018-02-18}}</ref> The previous weekend record was set in North America during the weekend of December 18–20, 2017, when the combined grosses of several films resulted in US$306 million led by ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]''{{'}}s US$248 million debut.<ref name="506F">{{cite web|url= https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2018/02/19/why-black-panther-and-monster-hunt-2-are-both-box-office-game-changers/#1d01a36e7bdb|title= Why 'Black Panther' And 'Monster Hunt 2' Are Both Box Office Game Changers|author=Scott Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=February 19, 2018|accessdate=February 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/top12sum.htm|title=BIGGEST WEEKENDS|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=February 20, 2018}}</ref> * The same weekend, China also set a new [[IMAX]] opening record when the combined IMAX earnings of the three films recorded US$15.1 million, led by ''Monster Hunt 2'' and ''Detective Chinatown 2'' (US$6.7 million).<ref name="190M"/> * During the first quarter of 2018, China overtook North America as the world's largest box office market for the first time, with China grossing {{US$|3.17 billion}} compared to North America's {{US$|2.89 billion}} during that quarter.<ref>{{cite news|title=China box office overtakes North America for first time|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/movies/china-box-office-overtakes-north-america-first-quarter-2018-n862371|work=[[NBC News]]|date=3 April 2018}}</ref><ref name="globaltimes">{{cite news|title=Local demands, local productions fuel China's box office bonanza: Hollywood experts|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1097177.shtml|work=[[Global Times]]|date=10 April 2018}}</ref> Despite declining revenue from Hollywood films, Chinese box office growth was driven primarily by domestic Chinese films, led by ''Operation Red Sea'' and ''Detective Chinatown 2'', along with non-Hollywood foreign films, led by Indian [[Bollywood]] films ''Secret Superstar'' and ''[[Bajrangi Bhaijaan]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Domestic films take lead at China's 2018 box office|url=http://www.china.org.cn/arts/2018-04/10/content_50856744.htm|work=[[China Internet Information Center]]|date=10 April 2018}}</ref><ref name="globaltimes"/>
====Studio records==== * [[Walt Disney Studios (division)|Walt Disney Studios]] became the fastest studio ever to reach $1 billion for the year at the domestic box office; it reached this goal in 117 days on April 27, 2018, beating its own record of 128 days set on May 7, 2016. * With ''Incredibles 2'', [[Pixar]] became the first animation studio to have three animated films (''[[Toy Story 3]]'', ''[[Finding Dory]]'') each surpass $1 billion at the worldwide box office.
{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}}
====Film records==== * ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]'' grossed $202{{nbsp}}million in its opening weekend and $242.16{{nbsp}}million over the four-day holiday weekend, breaking the record for a February opening weekend and a [[Washington's Birthday|Presidents' Day]] weekend, surpassing ''[[Deadpool (film)|Deadpool]]'' ($132.4{{nbsp}}million and $152.2{{nbsp}}million in 2016), and recording the biggest opening weekend and total for a film directed by a [[African Americans|black]] filmmaker, surpassing ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]'' ($98.8{{nbsp}}million by [[F. Gary Gray]] in 2017). It also became just the fifth movie ever to gross more than $200{{nbsp}}million [[List of highest-grossing openings for films#Biggest opening weekends in the U.S. and Canada|domestically]] in its opening weekend (joining ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'', ''[[Jurassic World]]'', ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'', and ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]''). On Monday, February 19, the film grossed another $40.17{{nbsp}}million, breaking the record for a Monday gross and surpassing ''Force Awakens'' ($40.11{{nbsp}}million on December 21, 2015).<ref name="hollywoodreporter">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/box-office-black-panther-climbs-historic-242m-bow-record-monday-1086456|title='Black Panther' Climbs to Historic $242M Bow After Record Monday|first=Pamela|last=McClintock|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> The subsequent $242.16 million four-day opening weekend became the second-biggest four-day gross ever, only behind ''The Force Awakens''' $288.07 million. On February 23&ndash;25, the film grossed another $111.7{{nbsp}}million, recording the second-biggest second weekend gross behind ''The Force Awakens'' ($149.2{{nbsp}}million on December 25&ndash;27, 2015) and becoming just the fourth film to gross more than $100{{nbsp}}million in its second weekend (joining ''The Avengers'', ''Jurassic World'', and ''The Force Awakens'').<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/weekend-box-office-black-panther-scores-record-108m-second-outing-1088212|title='Black Panther' Scores Record $108M in Second Outing|first=Pamela|last=McClintock|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> On February 27, the film became the first superhero origin film and the tenth film overall to gross $500 million domestically (doing so in 17 days, the third fastest film to reach the milestone behind ''The'' ''Force Awakens'' and ''The'' ''Last Jedi''), surpassing ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'' ($412.6{{nbsp}}million in 2017) to become the highest-grossing single character superhero origin film;<ref name="comicbook">{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/marvel/2018/02/28/black-panther-passes-wonder-woman-at-the-box-office/|title='Black Panther' Passes 'Wonder Woman' At The Box Office|first=Matthew|last=Mueller|publisher=ComicBook}}</ref> on March 9, the film reached $549.2{{nbsp}}million domestically, surpassing ''[[The Dark Knight (film)|The Dark Knight]]'' to become the highest grossing solo superhero film of all time. On March 16, the film became the seventh film to gross $600 million domestically (doing so in 31 days, the second fastest film to reach the milestone behind ''The Force Awakens''), and just the second superhero movie to do so (along with ''Avengers''). On March 24, the film reached a total domestic gross of $626-million to become the highest grossing superhero movie of all time, surpassing ''The Avengers'' ($623.4-million in 2012). On March 30, the film became the fifth film to gross $650 million domestically (doing so in 45 days, the second fastest film to reach the milestone behind ''Force Awakens''). On April 7, it reached a total domestic gross of $663.2-million to surpass ''[[Titanic (1997 film)|Titanic]]'' as the [[List of highest-grossing films in the United States and Canada|third-highest-grossing film in the United States and Canada]]. On August 3, it reached a total domestic gross of $700 million, becoming the third film to reach the mark. * On March 9&ndash;12, Ryan Coogler's ''Black Panther'' retained the #1 box office spot with a $40.8{{nbsp}}million fourth weekend (the fourth biggest, behind ''[[American Sniper]]'', ''[[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'', and ''The Force Awakens''), while [[Ava DuVernay]]'s ''[[A Wrinkle in Time (2018 film)|A Wrinkle in Time]]'' opened at the #2 spot with a $33.1{{nbsp}}million debut, marking the first time in history that the top two spots of a weekend were both held by [[African American|black]] directors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://geeksofcolor.co/2018/03/12/ryan-coogler-ava-duvernay-become-the-first-african-american-directors-to-take-the-top-two-spots-at-the-box-office/|title=Ryan Coogler & Ava DuVernay Become The First African-American Directors To Take The Top Two Spots At The Box Office|first=Britany|last=Murphy|publisher=GeeksofColor|date=2018-03-12}}</ref> * ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' grossed $258{{nbsp}}million in its opening weekend, breaking the record for biggest domestic opening weekend and surpassing ''The Force Awakens'' ($248-million in [[2015 in film|2015]]). The film grossed $641{{nbsp}}million worldwide opening weekend, becoming the first film ever to open with more than $600-million globally and surpassing ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]'' ($542 million in [[2017 in film|2017]]). On April 27, the film grossed $106 million in its opening day, the second-highest single day gross behind ''The Force Awakens'' ($119 million in [[2015 in film|2015]]) to become just the third movie ever to gross more than $100 million in a single day (joining ''The Force Awakens'' and ''The Last Jedi''); on April 28, the film grossed another $83-million, breaking the record for a Saturday gross and surpassing ''[[Jurassic World]]'' ($69.6 million on 13 June 2015); on April 29, the film grossed another $69.2 million, breaking the record for a Sunday gross and surpassing ''The Force Awakens'' ($60.5 million on 20 December 2015). The film became the second film of the decade to gross $2 billion, making the [[2010s in film|2010s]] the first decade to have two films gross $2 billion. * ''[[Secret Superstar]]'', an [[Indian film]] which released in China during January 2018, grossed $29.2{{nbsp}}million in its opening weekend there,<ref>{{cite web|title=Weekly box office > China (01/21/2018)|url=http://english.entgroup.cn/boxoffice/cn/Default.aspx?week=985|website=Entgroup|accessdate=January 27, 2018}}</ref> setting a record for an Indian film in China, surpassing ''[[Dangal (film)|Dangal]]''; [[Bollywood]] superstar [[Aamir Khan]] produced and starred in both films.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aamir Khan is China’s Secret Superstar, film earns Rs 174 cr in 3 days after Dangal’s massive success|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/aamir-khan-is-china-s-secret-superstar-film-earns-rs-174-cr-in-3-days-after-dangal-s-massive-success/story-jZYMTJWEtA6Ovt2HLk7oiN.html|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=January 22, 2018}}</ref> ''Secret Superstar''{{'}}s first-week gross in China was $47{{nbsp}}million,<ref>{{cite web|title=Daily Box Office > China (01/25/2018)|url=http://english.entgroup.cn/boxoffice/cn/daily/?date=01%20/25%20/2018|website=Entgroup|accessdate=January 28, 2018}}</ref> also a record for an Indian film in the country, again surpassing ''Dangal''.<ref name="scmp">{{cite news|title=Meet the Secret Superstar of China, from India|url=http://www.scmp.com/week-asia/society/article/2130746/meet-secret-superstar-china-india-aamir-khan|work=[[South China Morning Post]]|date=January 28, 2018}}</ref> Currently, ''Secret Superstar'' is the fourth highest-grossing foreign film in China for 2018 after ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'', ''[[Ready Player One (film)|Ready Player One]]'' and ''[[Rampage (2018 film)|Rampage]]'', ahead of Bollywood film ''[[Bajrangi Bhaijaan]]'' and Hollywood films including ''Black Panther'', ''[[Pacific Rim Uprising]]'', ''[[Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle]]'', ''[[Tomb Raider (film)|Tomb Raider]]'', ''[[Maze Runner: The Death Cure]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bajrangi Bhaijaan dethrones Secret Superstar to become third-highest-grossing Indian film of all time|url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bajrangi-bhaijaan-dethrones-secret-superstar-to-become-third-highest-grossing-indian-film-of-all-time-4411939.html|work=[[Firstpost]]|date=30 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Why Black Panther and other Hollywood films failed to unseat Aamir Khan's Secret Superstar at the Chinese box office|url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/why-black-panther-and-other-hollywood-films-failed-to-unseat-aamir-khans-secret-superstar-at-the-chinese-box-office-4413671.html|work=[[Firstpost]]|date=1 April 2018}}</ref> ''Secret Superstar'' also became one of the most profitable films of all time,<ref name="medium">{{cite news|last=Cain|first=Robert|title=‘Secret Superstar’ Is Hot On ‘Tiger’s Tail With Explosive ₹173 Crore/$27M China Debut Weekend|url=https://medium.com/@robcain/secret-superstar-is-hot-on-tiger-s-tail-with-explosive-173-crore-27m-debut-weekend-d1f513ac439f|work=[[Medium (website)|Medium]]|date=21 January 2018}}</ref><ref name="bloomberg-ren">{{cite news|last=Ren|first=Shuli|title=China's New Year Box-Office Boom Hides a Twist|url=https://www.bloombergquint.com/opinion/2018/02/22/china-s-new-year-box-office-boom-hides-a-sinister-twist|accessdate=26 February 2018|work=[[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]]|date=26 February 2018}}</ref><ref name="washingtonpost">{{cite news|title=Analysis: There's a Plot Twist to the Chinese New Year Movie Boom|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/theres-a-plot-twist-to-the-chinese-new-year-movie-boom-gadfly/2018/02/22/32318a2e-17ce-11e8-930c-45838ad0d77a_story.html|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=22 February 2018}}</ref> grossing {{INRConvert|965|c|lk=c}}<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/deepika-padukone-padmaavat-beats-aamir-khan-dhoom-3-and-salman-khans-tiger-zinda-hai-at-the-box-office/202889|title=Deepika Padukone's Padmaavat beats Aamir Khan's Dhoom 3 and Salman Khan's Tiger Zinda Hai at the box office|date=27 February 2018|work=[[Times Now]]}}</ref> worldwide on a [[Low-budget film|limited budget]] of {{INRConvert|15|c|lk=r}}, with over {{formatnum:{{#expr:900/15*100}}}}% [[return on investment]] (ROI).<ref name="medium" /><ref name="bollywoodlife3">{{cite news|last1=Aaglave|first1=Ganesh|title=Aamir Khan and Zaira Wasim's Secret Superstar crosses the Rs 750 crore mark in China|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/aamir-khan-and-zaira-wasims-secret-superstar-crosses-the-rs-750-crore-mark-in-china/|work=Bollywood Life|date=15 February 2018}}</ref> * ''[[Incredibles 2]]'' grossed $182.7 million domestically and $235.8 million worldwide in its opening weekend, setting records for the biggest domestic opening weekend for both Pixar and any animated film, (surpassing ''[[Finding Dory]]'', with $135.1 million in [[2016 in film|2016]]), the biggest worldwide opening for Pixar (surpassing Finding Dory), and the [[List of highest-grossing openings for animated films|biggest opening weekend worldwide for an animated film]] (surpassing ''[[Ice Age: Dawn of the Dinosaurs]]'', with $218.4 million in [[2009 in film|2009]]. It also set the record for the biggest opening for a PG rated movie (surpassing ''[[Beauty and the Beast (2017 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' with $174.8 million in [[2017 in film|2017]]). It became the first animated film to earn $500 million at the domestic box office, later the first animated film to earn $600 million at the domestic box office, earning just over $602 million and surpassing the previous record set by ''Finding Dory'' by over $100 million.<ref>{{cite web |title=Animation |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/genres/chart/?id=animation.htm |website=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=22 August 2018}}</ref> It is also the fastest animated film to gross $1 billion worldwide doing so in 46 days, surpassing ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]'' (49 days).
