{{Infobox military conflict |conflict=Battle of Bayrudh |partof= |image= |caption= |date=643/4 |place=Bayrudh, near [[Ahvaz|Hormizd-Ardashir]] |result=Muslim victory |combatant1=[[Rashidun Caliphate]] |combatant2=[[Sasanian Empire]] |commander1=[[Abu Musa Ashaari]] |commander2=Piruz |strength1=Unknown |strength2=Unknown |casualties1= |casualties2= }} The '''Battle of Bayrudh''' was fought between the [[Sasanians]] and the [[Rashidun Caliphate]] in 643/4. Before the battle took place, a group of Sasanian supporters rallied among a certain Piruz, who rebelled against the Rashiduns. They were, however, defeated at Bayrudh in 643/4.
