[[Image:Iimf logo sm.jpg|250px|thumb|right]] The '''InterHarmony International Music Festival''' is a summer [[Music Festival]] in [[Germany]] and [[Italy]]. The Festival is an annual intensive summer performance festival, which includes a concert series of international solo musicians and young performers, and an institute for students of solo, [[chamber music]], and [[orchestral]] playing. The festival hosts three sessions in two locations: [[Acqui Terme]], in the Province of [[Alessandria]] in [[Piedmont]], [[Italy]], and [[Sulzbach-Rosenberg]], [[Germany]] in [[Bavaria]].
==History== The InterHarmony International Music Festival was conceived in 1997, when cellist [[Misha Quint]], the Music Director and Founder, started his first International Music Festival in Blonay, Switzerland. This festival, the Intensive Cello Studies Abroad, was held at the Hindemith Foundation in Chalet de lacroix. Quint then opened the Soesterberg International Music Festival in Soesterberg, [[Netherlands]] in 1998.<ref name="Soesterberg International Music Festival">{{cite web | title = Soesterberg International Music Festival | url = http://www.klossclassics.com/soesterberg.php | accessdate = 2010-12-28 | dead-url = yes | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110713161123/http://www.klossclassics.com/soesterberg.php# | archive-date = 2011-07-13 | df = }}</ref> His festival in the [[Netherlands]] was a success and lasted for nine years. In the midst of the location in Soesterberg in 2000, the name, "InterHarmony", was born. [[File:InterHarmonyInternationalMusicFestivalGermany2012.jpg|thumb|InterHarmony International Music Festival in Sulzbach-Rosenberg, Germany 2012]] The Festival in 2000 in [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]] was the first to bear this name. Other locations later took it up. Some locations, such as Soesterberg and Sulzbach-Rosenberg also retained the location name within the city as a subsidiary of InterHarmony. The Sulzbach-Rosenberg location of InterHarmony opened in 2005 and was an immediate success with local audiences. The Hinterzarten, [[Germany]] locale in the [[Black Forest]] lasted from 2008 – 2011. There were two locations in the [[United States]]: [[The Berkshires]], [[Massachusetts]] from 2007- 2008, and [[San Francisco]], [[California]], at [[San Francisco State University]] in 2009.<ref name="The Berkshires Event Listing">{{cite web | title = The Berkshires Event Listing | url = http://www.cbs3springfield.com/community/events/18745334.html | accessdate = 2010-12-28 | dead-url = yes | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080725071622/http://www.cbs3springfield.com/community/events/18745334.html# | archive-date = 2008-07-25 | df = }}</ref><ref name="San Francisco Event Listing">{{cite web | title = San Francisco Event Listing | url = http://creativearts.sfsu.edu/events/2201/creativity-arts-and-your-gray-matter | accessdate = 2010-12-28 | dead-url = yes | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100824004054/http://www.creativearts.sfsu.edu/events/2201/creativity-arts-and-your-gray-matter# | archive-date = 2010-08-24 | df = }}</ref>
InterHarmony remains one of the only festivals of its kind to move around the world. Many students and artists-in-residence end up traveling to all the locations, and in the case of 2012, spending nearly six weeks at the festivals.<ref name="InterHarmony 2012 Dates">{{cite web | title = InterHarmony 2012 Dates|dead-url=yes| url = https://www.trombone.net/events/event.cfm?ID=3831 | accessdate = 2013-01-05 }}{{dead link|date=February 2018}}</ref>
The Festival has gained renown in [[Germany]] and brings international culture and artistry to its locations. For example, The U.S. Consul General spoke at the final concert where Misha Quint performed in 2008, and a Young Artist Showcase was given in the offices of the German Consulate in New York City in 2012.<ref name="U.S. Consul General in Bavaria">{{cite web |title=U.S. Consul General in Bavaria |url=http://munich.usconsulate.gov/upper_palatinate.html |accessdate=2009-03-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090422190128/http://munich.usconsulate.gov/upper_palatinate.html |archivedate=2009-04-22 |df= }}</ref><ref name="InterHarmony International Music Festival at the German Consulate General in New York City">{{cite web| title = InterHarmony International Music Festival at the German Consulate General in New York City| url = http://www.germany.info/Vertretung/usa/en/__events/GKs/NEWY/2012/05/03__Interharmony.html?archive=2010496| accessdate = 2009-03-14| dead-url = yes| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304053253/http://www.germany.info/Vertretung/usa/en/__events/GKs/NEWY/2012/05/03__Interharmony.html?archive=2010496#| archive-date = 2016-03-04| df = }}</ref> In 2010, [[Caitlin Hulcup]], a soloist from the [[Vienna Staatsoper]], and [[Christa Mayer]] from the [[Bayreuther Festspiele]], performed with the InterHarmony Festival Orchestra and the Forchheimer Kammerorchester, a [[Symphony Orchestra]] in [[Germany]].<ref name="InterHarmony International Music Festival">{{cite web | title = InterHarmony International Music Festival | url = https://www.interharmony.com/ | accessdate = 2010-12-17 }}</ref><ref name="Hinterzarten InterHarmony Final Concert Review">{{cite web | title = Hinterzarten InterHarmony Final Concert Review | url = http://www.suedkurier.de/region/schwarzwald-baar-heuberg/hinterzarten/Kurhaus-wird-zur-Musikoase;art372520,4411424 | accessdate = 2010-12-28|url-access=subscription }}</ref><ref name="Sulzbach-Rosenberg Public Inspired Article">{{cite web | title = Sulzbach-Rosenberg Public Inspired Article | url = http://www.oberpfalznetz.de/zeitung/2455372-129-publikum_inspiriert,1,0.html | accessdate = 2010-12-28 }}</ref><ref name="Sulzbach-Rosenberg Benefits from InterHarmony article">{{cite web | title =Sulzbach-Rosenberg Benefits from InterHarmony Article | url = http://www.oberpfalznetz.de/zeitung/2453864-129-zum_thema,1,0.html#top | accessdate = 2010-12-28 }}</ref><ref name="A Gift of Supernatural Music">{{cite web | title =A Gift of Supernatural Music | url = http://www.oberpfalznetz.de/zeitung/2454942-129-beschenkt_von_ueberirdischer_musik,1,0.html | accessdate = 2010-12-28 }}</ref>
==InterHarmony Concert Series in New York City== In 2012 InterHarmony International Music Festival opened the InterHarmony Concert Series with three concerts at the Weill Recital Hall at [[Carnegie Hall]] in New York City each year. The series showcases artist performers and advanced young artists who have previously performed at InterHarmony International Music Festivals in Europe.<ref name="InterHarmony Concert Series">{{cite web | title =InterHarmony Concert Series | url = http://www.carnegiehall.org/Calendar/2013/3/21/0800/PM/InterHarmony-Young-Artist-Showcase/ | accessdate = 2013-08-08 }}</ref>
==InterHarmony Outstanding Guest Artist series== In 2015 InterHarmony International Music Festival opened the InterHarmony Outstanding Guest Artist Series in its sessions in Italy and Germany. Famous musicians are invited to perform and give a master class to young artists. In 2015 the guest artists were violinist [[Vadim Repin]] and pianist [[Bruno Canino]] in Italy, and pianist [[Alfred Brendel]] gave a lecture in [[Sulzbach-Rosenberg]], Germany. The 2017 guest artists included [[Nikolaj Znaider]], [[Vadim Repin]], [[Shlomo Mintz]], [[Bruno Canino]], [[Alfred Brendel]], [[Christa Mayer]], and [[Boris Kuschnir]]. In 2018, guest artists include the conductors [[Gerard Korsten]], [[Christian Vasquez]], and [[Nicoletta Conti]], pianists [[Alfred Brendel]] and [[Joseph Banowetz]], and violinists [[Nikolaj Znaider]], [[Sergey Khachatryan]], [[Boris Kuschnir]], singer [[Christa Mayer]], and the Cosmopolitan Duo. <ref>{{cite web | title =InterHarmony Outstanding Artist Series | url =https://www.interharmony.com/guest-artist-series/index.html|access-date=2018-02-20 }}</ref> <ref>{{cite web | title =InterHarmony Outstanding Artist Series | url =http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/06/prweb12807159.htm |access-date=2018-02-20|date=2016-06-25}}</ref>
==Artist Performers== Each session of InterHarmony has at least forty guest artists. Previous guest artist faculty have included the following performers: {{Div col|colwidth=20em|rules=yes}} <ref name="InterHarmony Professors"> {{cite web | title =InterHarmony Professors | url = https://interharmony.com/Session1/index.html | accessdate = 2015-01-18 }}</ref> *[[Vadim Repin]], [[Violin]]<ref>{{cite web | title =Video of Performance | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uM_8fb2X7dY | accessdate = 2015-09-21 }}</ref> *[[Alfred Brendel]], [[Piano]]<ref name="Article">{{cite web | title =Violinist Vadim Repin, Pianist Bruno Canino, & Pianist Alfred Brendel to Join InterHarmony | url = http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/06/prweb12807159.htm | accessdate = 2015-09-21 }}</ref> *[[Bruno Canino]], [[Piano]]<ref name="Article"/> *[[Julian Rachlin]], [[Violin]]<ref name="Article2">{{cite web | title =Julian Rachlin violin joins InterHarmony International Music Festival | url = https://www.interharmony.com/guest-artist-series/Julian-Rachlin-violin | accessdate = 2016-09-23 }}</ref> *[[Jean-Bernard Pommier]], [[Piano]]<ref name="Article3">{{cite web | title =Jean-Bernard Pommier, piano, joins InterHarmony International Music Festival | url = https://www.interharmony.com/guest-artist-series/JeanBernard-Pommier-piano | accessdate = 2016-09-23 }}</ref> *[[Bella Davidovich]], [[Piano]]<ref name="Video of Performance">{{cite web | title =Video of Performance | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MQBktmDSYlw | accessdate = 2010-12-28 }}</ref> *[[Sidney Harth]], [[Violin]] and [[Conducting|Conductor]]<ref name="Event Listing for Sidney Harth">{{cite web |title = Event Listing for Sidney Harth |url = http://jpllmusicnews.wordpress.com/2009/07/06/interharmony-international-music-festival-san-francisco/ |accessdate = 2010-12-28 |dead-url = yes |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110718101300/http://jpllmusicnews.wordpress.com/2009/07/06/interharmony-international-music-festival